Philosophical Background and Evidential Support
The asynchronous, artifact-based evaluation model used by Lockbox AI is not a novel experiment — it is a direct application of conclusions drawn from decades of peer-reviewed research published in the most respected journals in psychology, behavioral economics, and organizational science. This body of evidence, which spans more than eighty-five years of accumulated data and includes work by Nobel laureates, demonstrates that traditional unstructured interviews are not merely ineffective but can actively degrade hiring decisions to outcomes worse than random selection from a qualified pool.

We believe transparency in this regard matters. Applicants deserve to understand not just what we ask of them, but why we ask it this way — and to see the evidence that supports the approach.
